- create a backend folder
- npm init
- entry point change it to server.js
- npm install express mongoose jsonwebtoken bcrypt cors dotenv body-parser multer stripe validator nodemon
- express - 
- mongoose - help us to connect to the db
- jsonwebtoken - auth system
- bcrypt - encrypt the users data and store in the db
- cors - permision to the frontend to connect with the backend
- dotenv - we can use the environment variable 
- body-parser - we can parse the data coming from the user
- multer - create image tool system
- stripe - addd payment gateways
- validator - check password or email ids is valid
- nodemon - when we save the server will be restarted
- in the package.json change scripts 'sevrer' : 'nodemon server.js
- create these folders: Config, Controllers, Middleware, Models, Routes, Uploads and .env
